SIMPLE: intercalation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intercalation
<hw>In*ter`ca*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>intercalatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>intercalation</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Chron.)</fld> <def>The insertion of a day, or other
portion of time, in a calendar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The insertion or introduction of anything among
others, as the insertion of a phrase, line, or verse in a metrical
composition;</def> <specif>specif.</specif> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <def>the
intrusion of a bed or layer between other layers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Intercalations</qex> of fresh-water species in some
localities.</q> <rj><qau>Mantell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intercarotid</ent>⟦br⟧
